'''Angolans in France''' consist of migrants from [[Angola]] and their descendants living and working in France.

== History ==
[[Angola|Angolans]] are one of the latest African community in France, and also one of the only [[francophony|non-francophone]] African community. However, there are a lot of Angolan people not only in Paris and [[Île-de-France|its suburbs]], but also in the rest of France. In 2013, a Confederation of Angolans in France was created.

