The annual '''Yoruba Arts Festival''' is an annual event which takes place in Hackney,[[London]], [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qymn1GNf1WE|title=Festival of Yoruba Arts at Clissold park London|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=qrwwAQAAIAAJ&q=festival+of+yoruba+arts&dq=festival+of+yoruba+arts|title=Ká má baa gbàgbé: a festival of Yoruba arts & culture|author=Yetunde Aina|publisher=Jadeas Productions|year=2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hackneygazette.co.uk/news/yoruba_festival_returns_to_stoke_newington_1_4165698|title=Yoruba festival returns to Stoke Newington|date=July 23, 2015|author=Emma Bartholomew|website=Hackney Gazette|location =United Kingdom|accessdate=October 28, 2016}}</ref>

The 9th edition of the festival returns to Clissold Park, Hackney, London on Saturday the 21st and Sunday 22nd of July 2018 celebrating the rich, colorful and vibrant Arts and Culture of the Yoruba's from around the world. Featuring Cultural performances, Workshops, Arts and crafts, Competitions, African Market, African food and live music from artists and bands dhowcasing the wide variety of popular Yoruba music such as Afrobeats, Juju, Highlife, Apala and Jazz.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asirimagazine.com/en/yoruba-arts-festival-returns-clissold-park-hackney-london/|title=Yoruba Arts Festival Returns to Clissold Park, Hackney London |author=|date=30 June 2016|work=ASIRI Magazine|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref> 

The Yoruba Arts festival returns for its 10th year at [[Clissold Park]] on the 15th & 16th of July 2019. The event is organised, produced and funded by the Yoruba Foundation, a UK registered [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit]] charity whose main objectives are to promote [[Yoruba people|Yoruba]] Arts and Culture through free community and charitable programs.

